{"id":"ev_cdb49aa71dd54986","runId":"run_262","type":"delegation","at":1782561014564,"data":{"workItemId":"wi_3564edbecccf4538","atom":0,"task":"Ticket 0077, atom 1 of a multi-atom plan: add the missing founder/Oscar-invokable command that triggers the founder-confirmation ticket-close for a run parked `awaiting-founder` with `ticketCloseDecision: 'ask'`. The daemon function `requestTicketCloseConfirmation` (packages/daemon/src/launcher.ts:1580) and its route `POST /runs/<runId>/ticket-close-confirmation` (packages/daemon/src/routes.ts:1045) ALREADY EXIST and already enforce the correct gate (ticketCloseGate, mode 'founder-confirmation', confirmedRunId === run.id). DO NOT touch the gate, the route, or requestTicketCloseConfirmation logic, and DO NOT add any second bypass around ticketCloseGate. This atom is pure CLI/chat wiring to that existing route.\n\nMake exactly these three additions:\n\n1) packages/cli/src/client.ts — add an exported helper mirroring `closeTicketViaDaemon` (around line 160): `confirmTicketCloseViaDaemon(baseUrl: string, runId: string, resolution?: string)` that GETs `${baseUrl}/auth/session` for bearer+csrf and POSTs to `${baseUrl}/runs/${encodeURIComponent(runId)}/ticket-close-confirmation` with a JSON body of `{ resolution }` only when resolution is provided (else `{}`). Return the parsed JSON. On a non-ok HTTP status, DO NOT throw — return the parsed JSON body so the CLI can surface the daemon's 409 reason (e.g. not-awaiting-ticket-close-confirmation); only throw on a genuine network/parse failure. Add a small result interface for the shape returned by requestTicketCloseConfirmation (ok, closed, reason?, error?, commitSha?, committedPaths?, runId?, ticketId?).\n\n2) packages/cli/src/run.ts — add an oz verb `cocoder oz confirm-ticket-close <runId> [--resolution <text>]`, modeled on the existing `oz close-ticket` block (lines 191-235). It REQUIRES a live daemon (this operates on the in-memory run store): probe with probeDaemon as the close-ticket block does; if the daemon is NOT alive, print an error to stderr explaining the daemon must be running for confirm-ticket-close and set process.exitCode = 1 (do NOT fall back to a local file path — there is none). Validate the runId positional and the `--resolution` option the same way close-ticket validates (`process.argv.includes('--resolution') && !resolution` => usage error, process.exit(2)). On success print a closed/commit line like close-ticket does; on a refusal (closed === false) print the daemon reason and set process.exitCode = 1. Add a `confirmTicketCloseUsage` const next to `closeTicketUsage` and add the new verb to the top-level `usage` string.\n\n3) packages/daemon/src/oz-chat.ts — add an oz-chat verb `confirm-close <runId>`. Add a command kind `{ readonly kind: 'confirm-ticket-close'; readonly runId: string }` to the command union (near line 18-21), add the action `type` literal if needed (line ~38), parse it in the verb section near `reconcile-close` (line ~122): `if (verb === 'confirm-close') return args.length === 1 ? { kind: 'confirm-ticket-close', runId: args[0]! } : { kind: 'unknown', hint: 'Usage: confirm-close <runId>' }`. Add a dispatch branch (mirror the reconcile-close dispatch at lines 249-501 and the archive-confirmation branch at 207-211) that calls `ops.requestTicketCloseConfirmation(ctx, { runId: command.runId })` and renders an ok/failed reply. You will need to add `requestTicketCloseConfirmation` to the `ops` interface/object that oz-chat uses (find how `requestArchiveConfirmation` / `requestReconciliationClose` are threaded through `ops` and add the new one the same way, importing from launcher.ts). Add `confirm-close <runId>` to the HELP_HINT string (line 12).\n\nAcceptance / what must not break:\n- `pnpm -w typecheck` (or the repo's typecheck) passes; the build compiles.\n- Run the daemon mutation tests that cover ticket-close-confirmation: `pnpm --filter @cocoder/daemon test` (the suite packages/daemon/tests/mutations.test.ts) stays green — you are not changing that route's behavior.\n- If oz-chat has a parser/dispatch unit test, run it; add a minimal parse test for `confirm-close <runId>` => `{ kind: 'confirm-ticket-close', runId }` and an arity-failure case if the existing tests establish that pattern (mirror the reconcile-close parse test). Do NOT invent a new test file if the pattern lives in an existing one — extend it.\n- The gate is reused, not duplicated: confirm-ticket-close must reach the close ONLY via requestTicketCloseConfirmation. No copy of ticketCloseGate logic in the CLI or chat layer.\n\nReport: the diff, the exact typecheck and test commands you ran with their exit status, and confirmation that requestTicketCloseConfirmation/route/gate were left unmodified."}}
